{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"10462a","heading":"Grants to State and Tribal courts to implement protection order pilot programs","label":"10462a Grants to State and Tribal courts to implement protection order pilot programs","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/stI/ch101/schXX","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Prior ProvisionsA prior was renumbered section 2104 and is classified to .section 2103 of Pub. L. 90–351section 10463 of this title","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Effective DateSection not effective until Oct. 1 of the first fiscal year beginning after , see , set out as a note under , Commerce and Trade.Mar. 15, 2022section 4(a) of div. W of Pub. L. 117–103section 6851 of Title 15"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Definition of eligible entity","label":"a Definition of eligible entity","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a State, Tribal, or local law enforcement agency;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a State, Tribal, or local prosecutor’s office;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a victim service provider or State or Tribal domestic violence coalition;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fa%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a provider of culturally specific services;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fa%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a nonprofit program or government agency with demonstrated experience in providing legal assistance or legal advice to victims of domestic violence and sexual assault;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fa%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the bar association of the applicable State or Indian Tribe;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"7","heading":null,"label":"7","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a/7","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fa%2F7","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the State or Tribal association of court clerks;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"8","heading":null,"label":"8","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a/8","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fa%2F8","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a State, Tribal, or local association of criminal defense attorneys;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"9","heading":null,"label":"9","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a/9","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fa%2F9","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"not fewer than 2 individuals with expertise in the design and management of court case management systems and systems of integration;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"10","heading":null,"label":"10","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a/10","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fa%2F10","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a/10/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a/10","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fa%2F10%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the field of domestic violence; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a/10/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a/10","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fa%2F10%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"issuing protective orders; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"11","heading":null,"label":"11","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a/11","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fa%2F11","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a judge assigned to the criminal docket of the State or Tribal court.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Grants authorized","label":"b Grants authorized","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Attorney General shall make grants to eligible entities to carry out the activities described in subsection (c) of this section.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Number","label":"2 Number","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Attorney General may award not more than 10 grants under paragraph (1).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"Amount","label":"3 Amount","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The amount of a grant awarded under paragraph (1) may be not more than $1,500,000.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Mandatory activities","label":"c Mandatory activities","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/c/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fc%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/c/1/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/c/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fc%2F1%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"modernize the service process and make the process more effective and efficient;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/c/1/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/c/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fc%2F1%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"provide for improved safety of victims; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/c/1/A/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/c/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fc%2F1%2FA%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"make protection orders enforceable as quickly as possible;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/c/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fc%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"develop best practices relating to the service of protection orders through electronic communication methods;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/c/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fc%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"ensure that the program developed under subparagraph (A) complies with due process requirements and any other procedures required by law or by a court; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/c/1/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fc%2F1%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"implement any technology necessary to carry out the program developed under subparagraph (A), such as technology to verify and track the receipt of a protection order by the intended party.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Timeline","label":"2 Timeline","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/c/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fc%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"implement the program required under paragraph (1)(A) not later than 2 years after the date on which the eligible entity receives the grant; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/c/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fc%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"carry out the program required under paragraph (1)(A) for not fewer than 3 years.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":"Diversity of recipients","label":"d Diversity of recipients","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a State court that serves a population of not fewer than 1,000,000 individuals;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/d/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/d/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fd%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"serves a State that is among the 7 States with the lowest population density in the United States; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/d/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/d/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fd%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"has a relatively low rate of successful service with respect to protection orders, as determined by the Attorney General;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/d/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fd%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/d/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/d/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fd%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"serves a State that is among the 7 States with the highest population density in the United States; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/d/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/d/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fd%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"has a relatively low rate of successful service with respect to protection orders, as determined by the Attorney General;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/d/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs10462a%2Fd%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a court that uses an integrated, statewide case management system;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/d/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10462a/d","so